📋 The Problem
You have two tables:
Employee table:
id | name  | salary | departmentId
1  | Joe   | 85000  | 1
2  | Henry | 80000  | 2
3  | Sam   | 60000  | 2
4  | Max   | 90000  | 1
5  | Janet | 69000  | 1
6  | Randy | 85000  | 1
7  | Will  | 70000  | 1
Department table:
id | name
1  | IT
2  | Sales
Task: Find employees who earn one of the top 3 unique salaries in their department.

WITH ranked AS (
    SELECT
        e.name       AS employee,
        e.salary,
        d.name       AS department,
        DENSE_RANK() OVER (
            PARTITION BY e.departmentId
            ORDER BY e.salary DESC
        ) AS rnk
    FROM Employee e
    JOIN Department d ON e.departmentId = d.id
)
SELECT
    department,
    employee,
    salary
FROM ranked
WHERE rnk <= 3;